<br>
If mob can't kill the target PC, and target PC isn't the class(es) ment to tank the mob then, in X seconds the mob will automaticaly move the next person to top of it's hate list that aggroed said mob. Be it a hit or a heal landing or anything else. That'd pretty much allow vi to make obsolete which classes tank which mobs. All vi need to do is add/subtract PC's from the list of X seconds rule.<br>
<br>
Example. <br>
Zone: Fear<br>
List of players who mob will only attack maximium of x seconds -in this case 20 seconds- <br>
Enchanters<br>
Clerics<br>
Bards<br>
Rogues<br>
Monks<br>
Wizards<br>
Mages<br>
Rangers<br>
Beastlords<br>
Necrmoancers<br>
Druids<br>
Shaman.<br>
<br>
This means the only classes not affected by the X list are warriors/paladins/shadowknights. <br>
<br>
If vi wanted to make those three classes unable to tank they'd add them to the X list.<br>
If vi wanted to make enchanters tank they'd take only them off the X list.<br>
<br>
To further complicate this as to avoid round house tanking vi could add a random Y factor where X seconds would be randomly between 5 and 30 seconds there by makeing round house tanking unreliable.<br>
<br>
--------------------<br>
<br>
<br>
Definition<br>
ROUNDHOUSE TANKING, is when pc's attack a mob and anyone getting hit by the mob turns off attack and those only gets some of the damage before the mob changes to a new target.<br>
<br>
<br>
-------------------<br>
<br>
The hope is through this code vi could make mobs require certain tanks. Currently monks and rangers and rogues are tanking many things once left only to war/pal/sk and usualy only war. With this code vi could decide exactly who's ment to tank which mob. It would also keep those who soloed mobs still able to solo them for they only have 1 name on the hate list.<br>
<br>
Think about it. Through the use of this veriable list and verable X factor vi could make mobs chaotic unless tanked by the class(es) vi wants tanking it.<br>
<br>
Hope this time I've made it easier to understand. If you get it what do you think of it?<br>
<br>
<br>
