<br>
Aggro change step 1 Give mobs a check list. &quot;If current target isn't a war/pal/sk/pet, (the list is made to be changeable on a mob by mob basis and is called the x list) then count z seconds and then put target at bottom of hatelist. z seconds would be a random number from 2-20 seconds on most exp mobs and 3-30 on most 61-70 lvl mobs and 1-5 on any rampageing mobs and 7-50 on any other boss mobs. Enchanters/Wizards/Magicians/Necromancers/Shaman/Druid then delay count 10 seconds.<br>
The list could change from mob to mob and zone to zone.<br>
<br>
This is a hard change to aggro. However it doesn't change the following things<br>
1 Aggro can still change before the clock finishes counting<br>
2 The soloing person is still the only one on hate list<br>
3 This doesn't hurt pet tanking for those who use it.<br>
<br>
This added line is only ment to be on mobs med 45th lvl and higher.<br>
<br>
Added Advantage. <br>
With the x list line being able to be set for each type of mobs verant could now make tanking stack in exp groups.<br>
<br>
An example<br>
<br>
In Karnor's Castle <br>
<br>
All live mobs would have only warriors on their x list. There by making the warriors the only class able to tank live mobs in that zone.<br>
<br>
All undead mobs would have paladins and shadowknights on their x list. There by making the only classes able to tank the undead mobs being paladins and shadowknights. <br>
<br>
These two things then requires groups wishing to use tanks to use both a warrior and a knight class. <br>
<br>
<br>
This same formula would allow you to make a few rare spawns only tankable by monks or rangers or beastlords ect. if the the story line called for it or in a specific case game balance required it. <br>
<br>
Also by removeing everyone on the &quot;x&quot; list vi could make a boss mob much harder with little alteration to current mob stats and perhaps even with mobs with lower stats. <br>
<br>
If warriors' AoE taunts threaten the balance of a mob using this &quot;x&quot; factor then a simple lowering of the random &quot;z&quot; seconds to a random seconds of 1-3 would make even that potential gimmick unusable to break that mob.<br>
<br>
<br>
That would fix the tanking situation without haveing to change the ac to godly amounts for traditional tanks. <br>
------------------<br>
